FBIS4-42641 "drweu109_j_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Italy Fini: Fascism `Cannot Return' Fini: Fascism `Cannot Return' LD0606150194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1430 GMT 6 Jun 94 LD0606150194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] Gianfranco Fini [leader of the National Alliance] said: "I am happy that [Israeli Foreign Minister] Shim'on Peres has said that there is no hostility on the part of the Israeli Government toward the Italian Government, and I am convinced that the concerns of [European Commission President Jacques] Delors will diminish in a short time when everyone has understood the values that are guiding both the government and the National Alliance." These are the values of "liberty, democracy, social justice, and tolerance," Fini explained, "in which all Italians believe." Fascism "ended in 1945 and cannot return," and "the National Alliance is neither a fascist or neofascist force."
